If I were a different person,

13:23.099 --> 13:24.799
would you have hit on me?

13:24.833 --> 13:26.351
I understand
what you're getting at, Lemon.

13:26.385 --> 13:28.703
There was a particularly
youth-oriented priest

13:28.738 --> 13:32.274
in my childhood parish who
went after everybody but me...

13:32.308 --> 13:35.076
Even fat Ralph, and he ate his boogers.

13:35.111 --> 13:37.145
I felt so unpretty.

13:37.179 --> 13:39.064
No, this isn't about appearance, Jack.

13:39.115 --> 13:40.848
Did nothing ever happen between us

13:40.866 --> 13:43.735
because I'm not fun?

13:43.786 --> 13:45.120
Good God, Lemon.

13:45.154 --> 13:47.122
Obviously, our relationship,
however you define it...

13:47.156 --> 13:48.490
Mentor/mentee...

13:48.524 --> 13:49.958
Sister-ployee/work oracle...

13:49.992 --> 13:53.211
Is more interesting
than some dating scenario.

13:53.246 --> 13:55.130
And obviously, to ruin what we have

13:55.164 --> 13:57.582
with a tawdry,
yet expert sexual encounter

13:57.633 --> 13:58.800
would've been a mistake.

13:58.834 --> 14:00.885
Obviously, but is it
the kind of mistake

14:00.920 --> 14:03.588
that I should have made?

14:03.623 --> 14:05.307
Tracy told me I haven't lived.

14:05.341 --> 14:07.842
You're allowing Tracy to criticize

14:07.876 --> 14:09.344
your life choices...
Tracy Jordan?

14:15.651 --> 14:17.435
Now what?

14:17.486 --> 14:18.687
But he's right.

14:18.721 --> 14:20.322
I haven't done anything impulsive ever.

14:20.356 --> 14:22.691
I don't have any tattoos
or broken bones.

14:22.725 --> 14:23.775
I've never been high,

14:23.826 --> 14:25.443
except for that choir trip to Montreal

14:25.494 --> 14:27.579
where I accidentally ate
a pound of marijuana.

14:27.613 --> 14:29.681
Also, maybe I was
never attracted to you

14:29.715 --> 14:31.366
because you're the kind
of person who finds a way

14:31.400 --> 14:33.752
to talk about herself while
lying in my dead mother's bed.

14:33.786 --> 14:35.170
Okay.

14:35.204 --> 14:36.621
Well, for the record, it's mutual.

14:36.672 --> 14:38.573
I wasn't exactly chomping at the bit

14:38.591 --> 14:41.092
to be with a middle-aged man
with crippling mommy issues.

14:41.127 --> 14:43.995
First of all,
it's "champing" at the bit.

14:44.030 --> 14:45.547
Horses champ.

14:45.581 --> 14:47.749
And second of all, I'm not going
to fight in bed with a woman

14:47.767 --> 14:48.850
I'm not even having sex with.

14:48.884 --> 14:50.435
Why? Is it weird?

14:50.469 --> 14:52.304
Of course it's weird.

14:52.355 --> 14:55.106
- Lincoln was super gay.
- Thank you.

14:55.141 --> 14:58.727
And I don't even want to think
about my mother.

14:58.761 --> 15:01.429
And I know those pots aren't flowers.

15:01.447 --> 15:04.399
They're my mother's vagina.

15:07.995 --> 15:11.636
Jay-Mo, I like to flouring a
joke about bjork's swan dress...

15:11.671 --> 15:12.671
Tired.

15:12.672 --> 15:13.672
I've seen dresses

15:13.673 --> 15:14.806
that look fly,

15:14.841 --> 15:16.558
but never dresses that can fly.

15:17.710 --> 15:19.227
I couldn't sleep at all last night.

15:19.262 --> 15:22.414
I've got this weird,
sick feeling in my stomach.

15:22.448 --> 15:23.515
Me too.

15:23.549 --> 15:25.233
It's the same feeling I got in 1997

15:25.268 --> 15:27.052
when that jury foreman
looked at me and said,

15:27.086 --> 15:28.153
"guilty!"

15:28.187 --> 15:30.739
And I had to close my water park.

15:30.773 --> 15:33.825
I forgot to make an opening
at the end of the slide.

15:33.860 --> 15:35.660
Is that what this is...
Guilt?

15:35.695 --> 15:36.945
I don't think so.

15:36.996 --> 15:39.414
I mean, what have we done
to feel guilty about?

15:39.448 --> 15:42.083
We don't care that
we made Kenneth lie, right?

15:42.118 --> 15:44.619
No! Come on!
It's Kenneth.

15:44.670 --> 15:46.922
Although he has been acting
a little different

15:46.956 --> 15:48.924
since yesterday.

15:48.958 --> 15:50.675
What?
Did I miss a spot?

15:50.710 --> 15:52.243
I don't care.

15:52.261 --> 15:54.679
All I care about is which jazz club

15:54.714 --> 15:57.632
I'm going to tonight.

15:57.683 --> 15:59.217
He's broken.

16:01.971 --> 16:03.772
Good morning, Jack.

16:03.806 --> 16:05.256
You sleep okay?

16:05.274 --> 16:07.559
Colleen's myna bird told me
you spent the night in the car.

16:07.593 --> 16:11.146
I slept fine.

16:11.197 --> 16:13.982
Before you leave,
I wanted you to have this.

16:14.033 --> 16:15.567
That was taken at the wrap party

16:15.601 --> 16:17.652
for our community center's
production of <i>Grease.</i>

16:17.703 --> 16:19.321
Your mother was Sandy.

16:19.372 --> 16:21.239
Well, the fourth Sandy.

16:21.273 --> 16:23.074
The first three died
falling off the car

16:23.108 --> 16:24.409
during "Summer lovin'."

16:24.443 --> 16:27.445
I don't know the last time
I saw her so happy.

16:31.667 --> 16:36.054
I'm glad she had you
to, take care of her.

16:37.790 --> 16:38.974
Lemon?

16:39.008 --> 16:41.142
Jack, you need to come
to Orlando and pick me up.

16:41.177 --> 16:44.145
I'm in Harry Potter world jail.

16:45.848 --> 16:48.850
Kenneth Parcell isn't signing
your precious affidavit.

16:48.901 --> 16:52.187
That is a Christmas card
from my estranged daughter.

16:52.238 --> 16:53.655
Tell him, Ken.

16:53.689 --> 16:56.024
If you've ever experienced
anything inappropriate at work,

16:56.075 --> 16:59.077
just tell the truth.

17:06.652 --> 17:07.919
Well, sir...

17:07.954 --> 17:09.588
No, Kenneth, you have
something in your teeth.

17:09.622 --> 17:11.489
I'm just trying to lick it off.

17:11.507 --> 17:14.626
Let me do it.
I'm your friend.

17:14.660 --> 17:16.711
Want to see a porno my cousin is in?

17:29.341 --> 17:31.175
To close a very important deal,

17:31.193 --> 17:32.953
I'm going to need
to loan you to David Geffen

17:32.979 --> 17:34.062
for the weekend.

17:34.113 --> 17:35.730
Why do I even take birth control pills

17:35.781 --> 17:37.649
if I'm always gonna be alone?

17:37.683 --> 17:39.150
You might as well take them, Kenneth.

17:39.184 --> 17:41.069
You take them!

17:41.120 --> 17:42.404
Take them!

17:42.455 --> 17:45.690
Now, for days
that weren't my birthday...

17:45.708 --> 17:47.993
Get me Philadelphia.

17:48.027 --> 17:50.495
'Cause I wanted to sound cool,
okay, Tucker?

17:50.529 --> 17:53.832
Fine, get me Gary Derekson.

17:57.303 --> 17:58.336
Well, I did it.

17:58.370 --> 18:01.056
I tried to live life, and it sucked.

18:01.090 --> 18:03.842
I came here without studying
the park map beforehand,

18:03.876 --> 18:05.644
which is how I ended up in a long line

18:05.678 --> 18:07.211
that turned out to just be
a crowd of people

18:07.229 --> 18:09.014
watching two owls have sex.

18:09.048 --> 18:10.432
Then the park started to fill up,

18:10.483 --> 18:13.384
but, I'm being spontaneous,
so I tried to cut the line

18:13.402 --> 18:15.603
for the flight of the hippogriff,

18:15.655 --> 18:18.273
which is when Duncan here caught me.

18:18.324 --> 18:19.941
What is the point, Jack?

18:19.992 --> 18:22.027
I am who I am,
and I'm never gonna change.

18:22.061 --> 18:23.445
I'll die full of regrets,

18:23.496 --> 18:25.080
like that time I sat
next to Richard Grieco

18:25.114 --> 18:27.615
on an airplane and just let him
read his <i>Hustlers</i>

18:27.667 --> 18:29.834
without ever telling him I was a fan.

18:29.869 --> 18:30.952
Lemon, you're wrong.

18:31.003 --> 18:32.537
People can change.

18:32.571 --> 18:35.006
Maybe tomorrow, maybe when you're 85,

18:35.041 --> 18:38.093
you'll find a reason to do something

18:38.127 --> 18:39.294
totally out of character.

18:39.345 --> 18:43.131
After all, that's what Colleen did.

18:43.182 --> 18:44.632
Not to make this about me,

18:44.684 --> 18:45.917
but are you admitting that I was right

18:45.935 --> 18:49.888
about your mother's
late-in-life lez-out?

18:49.922 --> 18:51.690
I just can't believe it.

18:51.724 --> 18:54.192
I know, and a woman
of color too... good for her.

18:54.226 --> 18:57.145
No, not that.
I can't believe she was happy.

18:57.196 --> 18:59.064
She was Mrs. silly.

18:59.098 --> 19:00.699
- Sketch idea.
- At the end,

19:00.733 --> 19:02.266
when she said she just wanted me
to be happy,

19:02.284 --> 19:03.605
I thought she was being sarcastic,

19:03.619 --> 19:05.436
because when I was growing up,
I thought people

19:05.454 --> 19:07.122
who wanted to be happy were weak...

19:07.156 --> 19:09.908
Hippies, Italians,
kindergarten teachers.

19:09.942 --> 19:11.626
What am I supposed to do with this?

19:11.660 --> 19:13.661
I don't know how to be happy.

19:13.713 --> 19:14.913
What are you talking about?

19:14.947 --> 19:16.548
That is enough
of your black Irish nonsense.

19:16.582 --> 19:17.799
Of course you're happy.

19:17.833 --> 19:19.634
It's never been the goal, Lemon.

19:19.668 --> 19:21.753
The goal has always been
money or prestige

19:21.787 --> 19:24.472
or, when playing hockey, the goal.

19:24.507 --> 19:26.457
Jack, in an hour, you are
flying to New York City

19:26.475 --> 19:29.928
on a private jet
to a party celebrating you

19:29.962 --> 19:32.147
as Kabletown's next CEO.

19:32.181 --> 19:33.542
It's everything you've ever wanted.

19:33.566 --> 19:36.518
And Colleen is looking down
on you right now,

19:36.569 --> 19:39.237
and you're happier
than you've ever been.

19:39.271 --> 19:42.357
Of course I am.

19:53.819 --> 19:54.919
Hello, Beverly.

19:54.954 --> 19:56.254
It's just Bev, Liz.

19:56.288 --> 19:57.705
My mother died while naming me.

19:57.757 --> 20:00.458
Well, I do have an opportunity
for an immediate placement.

20:00.492 --> 20:02.093
Really?
Okay.

20:02.128 --> 20:03.378
There is one issue.

20:03.429 --> 20:05.797
It's two children...
A brother and a sister,

20:05.831 --> 20:07.015
and we don't want to split them up.

20:07.049 --> 20:09.184
Two?
Boy, that wasn't our plan.

20:09.218 --> 20:11.102
<i>I know.
It's a lot to take on.</i>

20:11.137 --> 20:12.437
Why don't you discuss it

20:12.471 --> 20:13.688
